              "parts": [
                {
                  "text": "A fixed secret turns each nonnegative integer into a **glyph string** over ['\u2b21', '\u2b22', '\u2b23'].\n\nStructure (constant for this episode, all unknown):\n- Base-three expansion with **no leading-zero digit** except the integer 0.\n- The digit list is read either **most-significant-first** or **reversed** along the string.\n- Glyph at index 0 of that list uses one digit\u2192glyph bijection; index 1 uses another **independent** bijection on the same three glyphs; indices alternate.\n\n**Witness rows** (each row: glyph string, then the matching digit list in MSB-first standard form using characters 0, 1, 2 only):\n- `\u2b23\u2b22\u2b22\u2b23\u2b22\u2b22`  \u2192  `100100`\n- `\u2b21\u2b23\u2b21\u2b23\u2b23`  \u2192  `21211`\n- `\u2b23\u2b21\u2b21\u2b21\u2b22`  \u2192  `12220`\n- `\u2b23\u2b22\u2b22\u2b22\u2b23\u2b21`  \u2192  `100012`\n- `\u2b21\u2b22\u2b21\u2b21\u2b23`  \u2192  `20221`\n\n**Test glyph string:** `\u2b23\u2b23\u2b22\u2b21\u2b23`\n\nReply each turn with **one** line:\n- Probe: `MAP EVEN abc ODD def ENDIAN MSB` or `... ENDIAN LSB` where `abc` and `def` are each a permutation of 012 meaning, in glyph order ['\u2b21', '\u2b22', '\u2b23'], the digit carried by \u2b21, \u2b22, \u2b23 at even and odd indices respectively.\n- Final answer: `DIGITS zzz...` \u2014 MSB-first 0/1/2 digit list for the test string under the episode rules.\n\nAfter a `MAP` line you receive the **total digit mismatches** summed across all witness rows (exact Hamming; length mismatch counts per position). 0 means the probe matches every witness."
